				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I don't think there's a standard for save states, at least last time I looked. The format tends to change with each revision of an emulator too, e.g. if they emulate a new state they need to throw it in. (If you're lucky they threw a version number into the file format. If you're even luckier they might have documented it instead of having to deduce it from the source code.)<br /><br />SNES9X applies GZip compression to the whole file after packing it, so you need a GZ decompressor to even get inside (zlib will do).<br /><br />You'll probably find RAM dumps in blocks like you'd expect, but the layout of the file is going to be totally arbitrary, and everything else (registers, and all the various internal bits) gets very arbitrary indeed.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

